        "section_value": "Chief Complaint\nAnxiety and recent diagnosis of diabetes.\nHistory of Present Illness\nThe patient reports a history of anxiety, dating back approximately 10 years, managed with occasional over-the-counter remedies. He also reports increased stress levels related to recent diagnosis of diabetes. The patient reports excessive sugar intake, approximately 3 times the recommended amount, and reports experiencing anxiety related to his diabetes diagnosis. He denies chest pain or dizziness. The patient reports anxiety and pain. He denies nausea or chills.\nFindings\nThe patient has trace pitting edema to the lower extremities. Blood glucose levels are elevated.\nAssessment\nThe patient has newly diagnosed diabetes and reports anxiety. He has a history of anxiety and epilepsy.\nPlan\nA hemoglobin a1c test will be ordered. The patient will continue taking keppra. The patient will continue taking metformin 500 mg twice a day. Start physical therapy. Follow up in four weeks if symptoms persist.",
